title: GC volleyball eliminated
text: GC volleyball eliminated Gulf Coast’s hopes for a return to the state volleyball tournament were dashed Thursday night, as Pensacola State defeated the Lady Commodores 3-1 in Panhandle Conference play. Posted Oct. 22, 2015 at 10:53 PM Updated at 10:56 PM Posted Oct. 22, 2015 at 10:53 PM Updated at 10:56 PM PENSACOLA — Gulf Coast’s hopes for a return to the state volleyball tournament were dashed Thursday night, as Pensacola State defeated the Lady Commodores 3-1 in Panhandle Conference play. The Lady Pirates won 25-16, 25-16, 22-25, 25-18 to take the match victory and clinch the conference championship and a berth in the state tourney. Trailing the best-of-five season series 2-1, the Lady Commodores needed to win Thursday to stay alive. With the Lady Pirates winning, the final scheduled match will not take place next week. Pensacola State improved to 19-10 on the season, while Gulf Coast fell to 11-13. By THE NEWS HERALD
